# OS-layer CVEs in python/node slim-trixie images (Debian 13).
# Audit: revisit when Dependabot bumps the Dockerfile digest or Debian publishes trixie
# security uploads; verify with `trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL <image>` after rebuild.
#
# Tracker hub: https://security-tracker.debian.org/
# Typical removal check (in a built container):
#   dpkg-query -W systemd libsystemd0 libudev1 nghttp2 libnghttp2-14 libncursesw6 libtinfo6 libgnutls30t64 libssh2-1t64
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# CVE-2026-4105 — systemd-machined RegisterMachine / D-Bus (privilege escalation)
#   Debian trixie: open / no-dsa (narrow exploitability; requires permissive polkit).
#   Upstream fixes: systemd 257.12+ / 259.4 / 260.x; Debian sid builds use 260.1-1+.
#   Our image does not run systemd as PID 1; residual risk from libraries only.
CVE-2026-4105 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-29111 — systemd IPC / assert or stack issue on crafted unprivileged IPC
#   Debian trixie: open (systemd 257.9-1~deb13u1); patches in upstream 257.11+ etc., sid fixed.
CVE-2026-29111 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2025-69720 — ncurses infocmp stack overflow (CLI tool mitigations)
#   Debian trixie: open (no-dsa); fixed in Debian sid ncurses source 6.6+20251231-1 onward.
#   Headless CMDARR workload does not run infocmp; exposure is incidental library install.
CVE-2025-69720 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-27135 — nghttp2 DoS via session termination / malformed frame assertion
#   Debian trixie: open with libnghttp2-14 1.64.x; upstream fix nghttp2 1.68.1+,
#   Debian sid package nghttp2 1.69.0-1+. No trixie DSA yet.
CVE-2026-27135 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-4878 — libcap: TOCTOU / privilege escalation in cap_set_file()
#   Debian trixie: open (libcap2); other distros backported sooner; wait for security.debian.org.
#   EPSS low; CMDARR does not use cap_set_file() in normal operation.
CVE-2026-4878 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-33845 — GnuTLS: DTLS denial of service via zero-length fragment
#   Debian trixie: open (libgnutls30t64); few GA distros ship fix yet (scanner shows no fixed version).
#   EPSS moderate; workload is primarily TLS client/server via common stacks; revisit when Debian ships.
CVE-2026-33845 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-33846 — GnuTLS: heap OOB write in DTLS handshake fragment merge (same trixie gnutls epoch)
#   Debian trixie: vulnerable 3.8.9-3+deb13u2; fixed sid gnutls28 3.8.13-1 (bundled with GNUTLS-SA-2026-04-29)
CVE-2026-33846 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-3833 — GnuTLS: case-sensitive nameConstraints vs policy mismatch
CVE-2026-3833 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-42010 — GnuTLS: auth bypass via NUL character in username
CVE-2026-42010 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-42011 — GnuTLS: security bypass (name constraint handling)
CVE-2026-42011 exp:2026-09-01
#
# CVE-2026-7598 — libssh2: integer overflow in userauth_password (username/password lengths)
#   Debian trixie: open (libssh2 1.11.1-1); sid 1.11.1-3 fixed per tracker. CMDARR does not expose SSH client to untrusted callers.
CVE-2026-7598 exp:2026-09-01
